5000|$|August 1972 {{marked the}} end of CP/CMS, with IBM's [...] "System/370 Advanced Function" [...] announcement. This included: the new S/370-158 and -168; address {{relocation}} hardware on all S/370s; and four new operating systems: DOS/VS (DOS with <b>virtual</b> <b>storage),</b> OS/VS1 (OS/MFT with <b>virtual</b> <b>storage),</b> OS/VS2 (OS/MVT with <b>virtual</b> <b>storage,</b> which would grow into SVS and MVS), and VM/370 — the re-implemented CP/CMS. By this time the VM and CP/CMS development team had swelled to 110 people, including documenters. VM/370 was now a real IBM system, no longer part of the IBM Type-III Library. Source code distribution continued for several releases, however; see CP/CMS as free software for details.|$|E
