50|$|VSAM was {{introduced}} {{as a replacement}} for older access methods and was intended to add function, to be easier to use and to overcome problems of performance and device-dependence. VSAM {{was introduced}} in the 1970s when IBM announced <b>virtual</b> <b>storage</b> operating systems (DOS/VS, OS/VS1 and OS/VS2) for its new System/370 series, as successors of the DOS/360 and OS/360 operating systems running on its System/360 computer series. While backwards compatibility was maintained, the older access methods suffered from performance problems due to the address translation required for <b>virtual</b> <b>storage.</b>|$|E
